The paper deals with scheduling problems on parallel machines, which is a classic topic in computer science. The use of graphs to model the assignment restrictions is a common technique in this area, and the study of structural properties of these graphs is a well-established research direction. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are all relevant sub-categories. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and polynomial time approximation schemes, which are topics that fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
